In [128]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
cars_clusters=range(2,10)
cars_wss=[]

for k in cars_clusters:
    cars_k_means_model = KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    cars_k_means_model.fit(car_df_scaled)
    cars_wss.append(cars_k_means_model.inertia_)

plt.plot(cars_clusters, cars_wss, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Selecting optimal number of k by Elbow Method')
plt.show()

Assumptions of PCA¶

  1. PCA assumes a linear relationship between attributes
  2. There is no guarantee that the directions of maximum variance components will contain good features for analysis.
  3. It assumes feature set to be correlated and that the reduced feature set after applying PCA will represent the original data set in an effective way with fewer dimensions
  4. PCA assumes that components with larger variance correspond to better infomrmation for analysis and thus should be paid more attention and components with lower variance correspond to noise and thus can be ignored as well

Advantages of PCA¶

  1. Removes Correlated attributes
  2. Improves Algorithm Performance
  3. Reduces overfitting
  4. Improves Visualization
  5. Decreases storage requirements
  6. Decreases problems of dimensionality

Limitations of PCA¶

  1. PCA effectiveness depends upon the scales of the attributes.
  2. Changing scales of the variables can change the PCA
  3. Presence of skew in data with long thick tail can impact the effectiveness of the PCA
  4. PCA assumes linear relationship between attributes. It is ineffective when relationships are non linear 5.Information loss to a certain degree.
